                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/502a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-04T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Although every effort is being made to obtain the approval of Congress for
                    the financial settlement with Greece before the adjournment of Congress toward
                    the end of May, at present the prospects are not encouraging.</p>
                <p>The Department understands you do not intend to go on leave (granted you by the
                    Department on April 3) until after August 1. It seems clearly desirable for you
                    to remain in Athens for at least one month following the adjournment of
                    Congress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
